Chet,<br><br>
Make no mistake about it, I respect what you say.<br><br>
You should know as well as the rest here that spatz has been an antagonist on this site. Many of us tried to embrace his thoughts. In my case it was because I actually knew CO's in Vietnam, and protestors after I got home. I have since learned he has nothing in common with them.<br><br>
I have objected to the namecalling on *all sides* of this site, and I didn't take issue with spatz until he denied posting an insulting post to Art Varanelli. Subsequent posts by him reveal that he was the one who had made the post in question, and that he has written even worse posts accusing Vietnam vets, using the same worn out sterotypes. Forged messages have now become his specialty.<br><br>
What many people fail to realize is that there are those who have very passionate differences with those who did not serve- Cook being one. This is a reality that needs to be expressed on this site. I pointed out during the days of the Forum Discussions that right wing conservatives were not represented. <br><br>
Now they are. This site now accomodates their point of view. Why is that something that spatz can't stomach? As far as &quot;baiting&quot; spatz is right up there with the best of the baiters.<br><br>
As far as humor, I think that Ed Ramon has a good sense of humor. His expressions of American heritage are something that I also very much enjoy. I think his dissatisfaction with spatz comes from his perception that spatz is a phony. Mine too.<br><br>
Different points of view I can handle - bullshit lies I can't and won't put up with.
